Tokyo Exchange Aims to Launch Corporate Bond Market By July

-- B y   T a k a k o   I w a t a n i   a n d   A n n a   K i t a n a k a
-- 
2011-05-17T09:58:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/tokyo-exchange-aims-to-launch-corporate-bond-market-by-july-1-.html
The  Tokyo  Stock Exchange aims launch
a corporate bond market for professional investors by July after
receiving approval from Japan’s financial Services Agency, Chief
Executive Officer  Atsushi Saito  said today at a press conference
in Tokyo.  Professional investors are classified as individual
investors with over a year’s investment experience, investors
with more than 300 million yen in financial assets, and
institutional investors and corporations, according to a Tokyo
Stock Exchange release. Individual investors will need
permission from brokerages prior to investing, the statement
said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Takako Iwatani in Tokyo at 
